# Prompt Used in Antigravity:
You are a Senior Full-Stack Engineer.

We are building a production-ready web application step-by-step for a hackathon. 
DO NOT generate the full application at once because you get Hallucinated.

Follow STRICT incremental development.

----------------------------------------

# PROJECT OVERVIEW
Build a web platform called "HouseConnect" where users can:
- Post jobs for home services (plumbing, cleaning, electrical, etc.)
- View and browse contractors
- Book services with contractors
- Manage bookings
- Submit disputes/support requests

Tech Stack:
- Next.js (App Router)
- TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS
- Supabase (Auth + Database)

----------------------------------------

# DEVELOPMENT RULES (CRITICAL)
- Generate code ONLY for the current step
- Do NOT jump ahead
- Do NOT create unnecessary files
- Keep code clean and production-ready
- Use proper folder structure
- Use reusable components
- Ensure everything compiles
- Explain briefly what was done

----------------------------------------

# DATABASE (Supabase Tables)
We will use these tables:

users:
- id (uuid)
- name
- email
- created_at

contractors:
- id
- name
- service
- rating
- reviews
- price
- location
- verified
- created_at

jobs:
- id
- user_id
- category
- description
- location
- budget_min
- budget_max
- created_at

bookings:
- id
- user_id
- contractor_id
- date
- time
- status
- price
- created_at

disputes:
- id
- user_id
- booking_id
- type
- description
- status
- created_at

----------------------------------------

